Hello,

In between event days here- trying to get this working before playoffs.

We have a funnel into an end effector on an elevator. There is a LaserCAN sensor to detect when a coral is inside the end effector. In teleop, we use a command to intake coral, it runs the effector wheels at constant voltage and then stops them when the LaserCAN detects a coral (there is a delay, but we run the motors at such a speed that it stops in the perfect place including delay). This command works perfectly in teleop. However, it for some reason doesn’t work in auto. The LaserCAN has far too much delay, and the robot spits the coral all the way out before detecting- or sometimes moves on to the next command while the wheels are still running.

We are using pathplanner named commands and are also obviously over FMS - we found one other team using lasercan with similar issues at our event. It seems to be something fms/real field related.

WHAT WE’VE TRIED:

  • No changes yet: Coral spits out other end of effector. LaserCAN eventually trips and next path starts moving.
  • intake command for just auto that runs wheels slower: same result
  • test just auto intake with autonomous in pit with named command: works perfectly. Must be something with main field.
  • LaserCAN senses 140mm when no coral in robot. Senses ~35mm with coral in robot. Threshold used to be 100mm, change to 50mm. Result: got closer, the LaserCAN did trip sooner. However of the two times we tried, one spat the coral out and then moved on, and another spat the coral out but continued to run the effector wheels while the next path ran (lasercan never tripped??)

Literally don’t know what to do. We don’t have time to put a different sensor on the robot. It works in the pits and in teleop on the main field, but never works for auto on the main field. We would like this to start working before playoffs, so any help is appreciated and any ideas/ alternatives are greatly appreciated.
